  • Make a graph that is connected and find its minimum spanning tree and draw both graphs.

Make a graph that is connected and find its minimum spanning tree and draw both graphs.

10 1) 2) (MST: Minimum Spanning Tree)

10 10 

adj_mat <- matrix(rnorm(100),10,10)
adj_mat <- adj_mat + t(adj_mat)
adj_mat <- matrix(as.numeric(adj_mat > 1), 10, 10)

for(i in 1:10){
  adj_mat[i,11-i] <- 1
}
diag(adj_mat) <- 0
adj_mat

g1 <- graph.adjacency(adj_mat, mode="undirected")
plot(g1)

g1_mst <- mst(g1)
plot(g1_mst)

g2 <- graph.adjacency(adj_mat, mode="undirected")
E(g2)
## + 13/13 edges from 7520c9d:
##  [1] 1-- 2 1-- 8 1--10 2-- 3 2-- 4 2-- 7 2-- 9 3-- 8 4-- 7 5-- 6 6-- 8
## [12] 8--10 9--10
E(g2)$weight <- c(as.integer(runif(length(E(g2)), min = 1, max = 7)))
plot(g2, edge.label=E(g2)$weight)

g2_mst <- mst(g2, weight=E(g2)$weight)
plot(g2_mst, edge.label=E(g2_mst)$weight)
